Air Zone Report (2019-2021)

Air zone reports are prepared each year by the B.C. government to summarize the levels of air pollutants in broad reporting areas called air zones. B.C. is divided into seven distinct air zones based on

The reports compare pollution levels to the Canadian Ambient Air Quality Standards (CAAQS) and assign colour-coded management levels. The assignment of management levels also defines levels of actions that are recommended under the national Air Quality Management System.

Communities in the air zones have limited control over wildfire and other exceptional events, as well as pollutants from far beyond its borders. These transboundary flows and exceptional events are presented in this report but are not included when communities and air zones are assessed for achievement of CAAQS and management levels. This helps communities focus on actions from local sources of pollution.
